        <Parent_String>aerophone components [300190947], sound device components [300205017], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood or metal discs, cylinders, or cup-shaped attachments located below the double reed in some European and most non-European double reed instruments, serving as a lip rest. The reed is taken into the player's mouth and the lips pressed against the pirouette.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Houten of metalen schijven, cilinders, of komvormige aanhechtsels bevestigd onder de double reed in sommige Europese en de meeste niet-Europese dubbelriet-instrumenten, die dienst doen als een liprest. De muzikant neemt het riet in de mond en drukt de lippen tegen de pirouette.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052453/Algemene muziekencyclopedie (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>木頭或金屬製的圓盤物、圓柱物或杯狀附著物，裝置在雙簧底下，出現於某些歐洲或大部分歐洲以外地區的雙簧樂器上，以作為唇架之用，吹奏者將簧片含入口中，而嘴唇則貼住吹嘴圓座。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Scheibe, Zylinder oder becherförmiger Aufsatz aus Holz oder Metall unterhalb des Doppelrohrblatts bei einigen europäischen und den meisten nichteuropäischen Doppelrohrblattinstrumenten, als Lippenstütze dienend. Das Rohrblatt wird in der Mundhöhle des Spielers gehalten und die Lippen werden gegen die Pirouette gepresst.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
